columns=['Density\n(P/Km2)','Agricultural Land( %)','Land Area(Km2)','Armed Forces size','Co2-Emissions',
        'CPI','CPI Change (%)','Forested Area (%)','Gasoline Price','GDP','Gross primary education enrollment (%)',
        'Gross tertiary education enrollment (%)','Minimum wage','Out of pocket health expenditure','Population',
        'Population: Labor force participation (%)','Tax revenue (%)','Total tax rate','Unemployment rate',
        'Urban_population']
data[columns]=data[columns].applymap(lambda x: float(str(x).replace(',','').replace('%','').
                                                        replace('$','')))

Handling missing values¶

In [41]:
# impute numerical columns with mean 

numerical_col=data.select_dtypes(include=['float64'])
numerical_col=numerical_col.columns[numerical_col.isnull().any()]
data[numerical_col]=data[numerical_col].fillna(data[numerical_col].mean())
In [42]:
#impute categorical columns with mode
In [46]:
# Impute categorical columns with mode
categorical_columns = data.select_dtypes(include=['object'])
categorical_columns = categorical_columns.columns[categorical_columns.isnull().any()]
data[categorical_columns] = data[categorical_columns].fillna(data[categorical_columns].mode().iloc[0])

fig, axes = plt.subplots(nrows=1, ncols=2, figsize=(14, 9))

# Plot for high unemployment countries
sns.barplot(data=top20_country, x='Country', y='Land Area(Km2)', palette='bright', ax=axes[0])
axes[0].set_title('Top 20 largest Countries')
axes[0].set_xlabel('Country')
axes[0].set_ylabel('Land Area(Km2)')
axes[0].set_xticklabels(axes[0].get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
for p in axes[0].patches:
    axes[0].annotate(f'{p.get_height():.2f}%', (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2, p.get_height()),
                     ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10, color='black', xytext=(0, 5),
                     textcoords='offset points', rotation = 45)

# Plot for low unemployment countries
sns.barplot(data=low20_country, x='Country', y='Land Area(Km2)', palette='rainbow', ax=axes[1])
axes[1].set_title('smallest  Countries')
axes[1].set_xlabel('Country')
axes[1].set_ylabel('Land Area(Km2)')
axes[1].set_xticklabels(axes[1].get_xticklabels(), rotation=45, ha='right')
for p in axes[1].patches:
    axes[1].annotate(f'{p.get_height():.2f}%', (p.get_x() + p.get_width() / 2, p.get_height()),
                     ha='center', va='bottom', fontsize=10, color='black', xytext=(0, 5),
                     textcoords='offset points', rotation = 45)

# Show the plots
plt.show()
